<HEAD>Shultz Gets Pope's Blessing for Mideast Mission</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Israel, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By STEPHEN R. WILSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> today received Pope <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>'s blessing on the eve of his new <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> peace mission. The pontiff stressed any accord must respect the `` legitimate rights'' of both <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and the Palestinians. `` God bless your efforts,'' the <PERSON> pope </PERSON> told <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> following their 30-minute private meeting in the papal library. `` I go from here to the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> with your blessing to sustain the effort'' to spur the <LOCATION> Arab-Israeli </LOCATION> peace process, <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> responded in front of reporters and photographers. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> leaves for <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> on Sunday on the first part of a trip that will also take him to <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Saudi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arabia </LOCATION>. His trip to the region last month failed to bring an agreement. <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> spokesman <PERSON> Joaquin </PERSON> <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> said the talks focused on the two mens' `` common preoccupation for international peace,'' specifically <LOCATION> East-West </LOCATION> relations, `` the continuing grave situation'' in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> and developments in <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>. The pope `` insisted on the legitimate rights of the Palestinian people and on the moral duty to find a solution that also takes into account the legitimate rights of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>,'' the spokesman said. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> voiced `` great interest in the efforts under way for the search, obligatory for everyone, of a process that opens the way to solutions acceptable to all,'' <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> said. The pope has frequently spoken in favor of a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> homeland. The <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> does not have diplomatic relations with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> officials have cited the Palestinian question, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s unsettled boundaries and the status of <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> as reasons for the absence of ties The <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> does not have diplomatic relations with <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> either. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>, who is <PERSON> Episcopalian </PERSON>, brought to the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> today an entourage of 31 people, including his wife, <PERSON> Helena </PERSON>, a Roman Catholic. After a salute in the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION>'s marbled, frescoed Clementine room by seven Swiss guards in multi-colored uniforms designed by <PERSON> Michelangelo </PERSON>, <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> was ushered into the pope's chambers by Archbishop <PERSON> Dino </PERSON> <PERSON> Monduzzi </PERSON>, head of the papal household. Following the audience, the two were joined by Mrs. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>, wearing a black dress and a black lace mantilla over her head, and the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> ambassador to the Holy See, <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Shakespeare </PERSON>, and his 21-year-old daughter, <PERSON> Fredericka </PERSON>. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON>, wearing white robes, presented <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> with a framed sketch by Italian artist <PERSON> Lello </PERSON> <PERSON> Scorzelli </PERSON>. He gave pontifical medals and rosaries to the others. The group then moved to the <LOCATION> Salome </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Throne </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Room </LOCATION>, where the <PERSON> pope </PERSON> shook hands with the rest of the delegation, including <ORGANIZATION> Secret </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> agents and <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Redman </PERSON>. The pope wished them all a happy Easter. It was <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>'s third meeting at the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> with <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON>. He and his wife visited the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> in 1986 for Easter. The previous meeting was in December 1982. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> and his wife are scheduled to attend the pope's Easter Mass in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peter </LOCATION>'s Square on Sunday morning.
