<HEAD>Postage Charges Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Mailing a letter costs more starting Sunday, as new postage rates go into effect. It will cost 25 cents to mail first-class letters, up 3 cents. The second ounce of first-class mail also rises 3 cents, to 20 cents. But postal cards are up only a penny, to 15 cents. The rate increases cover most classes of mail, with larger hikes for advertising and periodicals than for letters.
