<SECOND>AM-BRF--Daylight Time,50</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Daylight-saving time is back. The change, moving clocks ahead one hour, occurred at 2 a.m. Sunday. Folks who forgot likely found themselves an hour late for church or other activities. Daylight time will remain in effect until Oct. 30 this year, when that hour of lost sleep will be returned.
