<HEAD>Shultz Calls Again For Ouster Of Noriega's Ouster</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Panama</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BARRY SCHWEID</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Diplomatic Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> insisted Saturday on the ouster of Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> but sidestepped a report that he had recommended kidnapping the Panamanian strongman. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> predicted he would `` see a little headway'' when he again takes up his plan for <LOCATION> Mideast </LOCATION> peace talks next week with <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> leaders. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> called on Palestinians to participate in the negotiations, but he again ruled out talks with the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>. `` Obviously, there are some we wo n't meet with,'' <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> said as he reiterated the 13-year-old <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> policy of not dealing with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> until it accepts <ORGANIZATION> Irael </ORGANIZATION>'s right to exist. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> held the news conference after receiving Pope <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>'s blessing at the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> for his new venture in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> that begins Sunday evening in <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>. The pope stressed any accord must respect the `` legitimate rights'' of both Israelis and Palestinians. The <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> does not have diplomatic relations with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> nor does it recognize its control of once-divided <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>, the Israeli capital. The <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> reported Friday that <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> recommended kidnapping <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> and fomenting a military coup coordinated with the <ORGANIZATION> Ce