B- held for a few days,'' he said. The Nicaraguan Resistance, the Contra umbrella group, also said Saturday the government has refused to sell necessary printing materials to the opposition <ORGANIZATION> La </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Prensa </ORGANIZATION> newspaper `` while it continues granting all paper and other materials for publication to the other newspapers,'' in violation of the pact's condition for full press freedom in <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>. Under the terms of the cease-fire pact, the <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION> said they would release all 3,300 political prisoners gradually, the last coming after the 60-day cease-fire period ended June 1. The government also pledged full freedom of expression. The Contras pledged to accept only humanitarian aid through a neutral organization. That clause, according to the Sandinistas, means the rebels can receive only civilian clothes, food and medicine and that it must come through an organization such as the <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION>.
